ent">thresh</code></a>)</code></span>
                returns the edges found in the grayscale or binary volume <=
code class=3D"argument">V</code>
                using the approximate Canny method. The approximate Canny m=
ethod finds edges by
                looking for local maxima of the gradient of <code class=3D"=
argument">V</code>.
                    <code class=3D"literal">edge3</code> calculates the gra=
dient using the derivative of a
                Gaussian smoothed volume.</p><p>The approximate Canny metho=
d uses two thresholds to detect strong and weak edges,
                and includes the weak edges in the output only if they are =
connected to strong
                edges. This method is more likely than the Sobel method to =
detect true weak
                edges.</p></div></div><div class=3D"description_element"><p=
