ode></a> =3D edge3(<a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b=
/images/ref/edge3.html#d126e104677" class=3D"intrnllnk"><code class=3D"argu=
ment">V</code></a>,"Sobel",<a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/release=
s/R2023b/images/ref/edge3.html#d126e104720" class=3D"intrnllnk"><code class=
=3D"argument">thresh</code></a>)</code></span>
                accepts an intensity or a binary volume <code class=3D"argu=
ment">V</code> and returns a binary
                volume <code class=3D"argument">BW</code> with <code class=
=3D"literal">1</code>s where the function finds
                edges in <code class=3D"argument">V</code> and <code class=
=3D"literal">0</code>s elsewhere.</p><p>The Sobel method finds edges using =
